<p>Paul Gauguin to Vincent van Gogh. Le Pouldu, on or about Thursday, 20 March 1890.</p>
<note type="ongoingTopic" n="1">
<p>Entry for the 1890 Indépendants exhibition <ref target="let854.xml">(854)</ref>
                            </p>
                        </note>
<note type="ongoingTopic" n="2">
<p>Fourth attack in Saint-Rémy <ref target="let857.xml">(857)</ref>
                            </p>
                        </note>
                    </vg:letContents>
<note type="sourceStatus" xml:id="sourceStatus">
<p>Original manuscript</p>
                    </note>
<note type="location" xml:id="location">
<p>Amsterdam, Van Gogh Museum, inv. no. b872 V/1962</p>
                    </note>
<note type="date" xml:id="date">
<p>The letter must have been written about the same time as Theo’s <ref target="let858.xml">letter 858</ref> of 19 March 1890, considering that both letters talk about the works by Van Gogh shown at the recently opened exhibition of the Indépendants. In this letter Gauguin suggests the exchange that Theo had already mentioned in his letter. Because a more precise dating is impossible, we have dated the present letter to about Thursday, 20 March 1890.</p>
                    </note>
